# Experiment Tracking Standards

This document defines standards for tracking ML experiments to ensure reproducibility and comparability.

---

## Experiment Naming Convention

```
{project}/{model_type}/{experiment_name}_{YYYYMMDD}

Example: fraud-detection/xgboost/feature_ablation_20260215
```

---

## Required Metadata Per Run

### Mandatory Fields

| Field | Description | Example |
|-------|-------------|---------|
| run_name | Human-readable name | "baseline_xgb_v2" |
| experiment_name | Parent experiment | "fraud_detection_q1" |
| model_type | Algorithm family | "xgboost", "lstm", "random_forest" |
| data_version | Hash or version of training data | "v2.3" or "sha256:abc123" |
| code_version | Git commit SHA | "a1b2c3d4" |
| author | Who ran the experiment | "team-ml" |
| hypothesis | What you expect to learn | "Adding feature X improves recall" |

### Hyperparameters

- [ ] All hyperparameters logged (including defaults)
- [ ] Search space documented if HPO was used
- [ ] Best hyperparameters highlighted
- [ ] Random seed logged

### Metrics

- [ ] Primary metric logged at each epoch/iteration
- [ ] Validation metrics logged separately from training metrics
- [ ] Final test set metrics logged once (not used for selection)
- [ ] Confusion matrix or classification report logged as artifact

```python
import mlflow

with mlflow.start_run(run_name="baseline_xgb_v2"):
    mlflow.log_params({
        "model_type": "xgboost",
        "learning_rate": 0.1,
        "max_depth": 6,
        "n_estimators": 100,
        "data_version": data_hash,
        "random_seed": 42,
    })

    mlflow.log_metrics({
        "train_auc": train_auc,
        "val_auc": val_auc,
        "val_precision": val_precision,
        "val_recall": val_recall,
    })

    mlflow.log_artifact("confusion_matrix.png")
    mlflow.log_artifact("feature_importance.json")
```

