## Artifact Management

### Required Artifacts

| Artifact | Format | When to Log |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| Model binary | pickle, ONNX, SavedModel | Every run |
| Feature importance | JSON or CSV | Every run |
| Confusion matrix | PNG or JSON | Classification tasks |
| Learning curves | PNG | Training runs |
| Data sample | Parquet (100 rows) | Feature engineering experiments |
| Config file | YAML | Every run |

### Artifact Naming

```
{run_id}/
  model/           # Serialized model
  metrics/          # Metric plots and CSVs
  artifacts/        # Additional artifacts
  config.yaml       # Full configuration
```

---

## Comparison and Analysis

### Before Starting a New Experiment

1. Query existing runs for the same experiment name
2. Identify the current best run
3. Document why a new approach is needed

### After Completing an Experiment

1. Compare against baseline run
2. Log comparison metrics (delta from baseline)
3. Document whether the hypothesis was supported or refuted
4. Update the experiment README with findings

---

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Why It's Bad | Correct Approach |
|--------------|--------------|------------------|
| No run name | Can't find results later | Always name runs descriptively |
| Missing data version | Can't reproduce | Hash or version all datasets |
| Test set used for selection | Overfitting to test set | Use validation set for selection |
| No hypothesis documented | Aimless experimentation | State hypothesis before running |
| Logging only final metrics | Can't debug training | Log per-epoch metrics |
